How to setup up your path to run your bash scripts May 13, 2016

Setup your bin directory should be a subdirectory of you home folder.
/home/you/bin

Export your path to allow you to run your programs from anywhere in the terminalexport PATH=$PATH:/home/you/bin

View all your paths
echo PATH$

I am setting up a git directory named 'bin' to save all of my bash scripts.


